-- Investec Falls in Johannesburg After Saying Impairments Remain `Elevated'
-- Vernon Wessels
-- 2010-07-30T07:30:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-30/investec-falls-in-johannesburg-after-saying-impairments-remain-elevated-.html

          
          
             Investec Ltd., the private bank and
wealth manager, declined in Johannesburg trading after saying
impairments remained at “elevated levels” in the three months
through June.  
 The stock slipped as much as 1.39 rand, or 2.3 percent, to
59.61 rand, and was trading at 59.92 rand as of 9:28 a.m. local
time.  
          
          


  


        